# Clusters — all-purpose vs. job

- A **cluster** = cloud VMs running Spark: one driver + one or more workers
- **All-purpose** — interactive, multi-user, stays up for dev in notebooks; higher rate
- **Job cluster** — created per run, terminates when done; isolated, cheaper rate
- **Rule** — dev & exploration → all-purpose; scheduled production → job clusters
- **Anti-pattern** — production jobs on all-purpose: costs more, loses per-run isolation
